// Delivery ID/Access ID Generator for delivery/pickup drivers at MEL04 & MEL05.

Print "Welcome to Delivery/Access ID Generator".

print menu:
	(1)  MEL04 ID Generator
	(2)  MEL05 ID Generator
	(0)  Quit Program

For (1) MEL04 selection:

	Request user input details:
		print options:
			Select one of the following: 
			
			'P' for Purchase Order deliveries
			'RMA' for RMA deliveries/pickups
			'T' for Transfer Order deliveries/pickups 
			'O' for all Other deliveries/pickups
			
			if 'P' (to upper case) is selected:
				create ID string
				delID = "MS04P"
				
				generate random 3 integers
					these 3 ints can't already exist in Delivery ID file 'Delivery ID Log.txt'
					loop again until the 3 ints are not in file
					int nums = 3 generated integers
					return nums
					
				turn nums into string data type
				
				append nums to delID
				print delID
				save delID to 'Delivery ID Log.txt'
				return to main menu
				

			if 'RMA' (to upper case) is selected:
				create ID string
				delID = "MS04RMA"
				
				generate random 3 integers
					these 3 ints can't already exist in Delivery ID file 'Delivery ID Log.txt'
					loop again until the 3 ints are not in file
					int nums = 3 generated integers
					return nums
					
				turn nums into string data type
				
				append nums to delID
				print delID
				save delID to 'Delivery ID Log.txt'
				return to main menu
				
				
			if 'T' (to upper case) is selected:
				create ID string
				delID = "MS04T"				
			
				generate random 3 integers
					these 3 ints can't already exist in Delivery ID file 'Delivery ID Log.txt'
					loop again until the 3 ints are not in file
					int nums = 3 generated integers
					return nums
					
				turn nums into string data type
				
				append nums to delID
				print delID
				save delID to 'Delivery ID Log.txt'
				return to main menu			
				
				
			if 'O' (to upper case) is selected:
				create ID string
				delID = "MS04O"
				
				generate random 3 integers
					these 3 ints can't already exist in Delivery ID file 'Delivery ID Log.txt'
					loop again until the 3 ints are not in file
					int nums = 3 generated integers
					return nums
					
				turn nums into string data type
				
				append nums to delID
				print delID
				save delID to 'Delivery ID Log.txt'
				return to main menu	
				
